.TH SUTURE-REV_PARSE "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-rev\-parse \- Parse revision names to hashes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture rev\-parse [\\fIoptions\\fR] [\\fIrefs\\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse revision names to hashes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-short
Output abbreviated hash
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-verify
Verify the ref exists (error if not)
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture rev\-parse HEAD       # Resolve HEAD to full hash
suture rev\-parse \\\-\\\-short HEAD  # Abbreviated hash
suture rev\-parse \\\-\\\-verify main  # Verify ref exists
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
